<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="120" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1040,2039]" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1112,1138]" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Superficially 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[482,573,1112,1138]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clara">
<emphasis box="[482,573,1112,1138]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">B. clara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[722,825,1112,1138]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kareni">
<emphasis box="[722,825,1112,1138]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">B. kareni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[881,1022,1112,1138]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenebrosa">
<emphasis box="[881,1022,1112,1138]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">B. tenebrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1038,1140,1112,1138]" captionStart="FIGURES 1-8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1792,1816]" captionTargetBox="[177,1422,239,1749]" captionTargetId="figure-24@2.[151,1435,181,1768]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1-8. Bellulia spp., adults. 1. B. kareni (after Fibiger 2008); 2. B. tenebrosa sp. n., holotype, Cambodia; 3. B. clara sp. n., holotype, Cambodia; 4. B. mariannae (after Fibiger 2008); 5. B. parabella (after Fibiger 2008); 6. B. hanae (after Fibiger 2008); 7. B. jiaxuanae sp. n., holotype, China; 8. B. bibella (after Fibiger et al. 2011)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561449" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561449/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
), but can be distinguished by the narrower forewing (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[484,587,1148,1174]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kareni">
<emphasis box="[484,587,1148,1174]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">B. kareni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[642,783,1148,1174]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenebrosa">
<emphasis box="[642,783,1148,1174]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">B. tenebrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the forewing relatively broader); the basal line is distinct, slightly arched (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[372,478,1184,1210]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kareni">
<emphasis box="[372,478,1184,1210]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">B. kareni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[538,682,1184,1210]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenebrosa">
<emphasis box="[538,682,1184,1210]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">B. tenebrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is rather indistinct, and weakly waved); the antemedial line is smoothly curved (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[380,482,1220,1246]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kareni">
<emphasis box="[380,482,1220,1246]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">B. kareni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[533,672,1220,1246]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenebrosa">
<emphasis box="[533,672,1220,1246]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">B. tenebrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is waved); postmedial line is very narrow, with a small dark brown patch on the costal area (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[458,559,1256,1282]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kareni">
<emphasis box="[458,559,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">B. kareni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[613,753,1256,1282]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenebrosa">
<emphasis box="[613,753,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">B. tenebrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
postmedial line has a large dot in the costal area); the subterminal line is thin (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[387,489,1292,1318]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kareni">
<emphasis box="[387,489,1292,1318]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">B. kareni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[544,684,1292,1318]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenebrosa">
<emphasis box="[544,684,1292,1318]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">B. tenebrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is broad and more grainy in appearance); the hindwing is lighter than forewing (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[355,458,1328,1354]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kareni">
<emphasis box="[355,458,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">B. kareni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[513,654,1328,1354]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenebrosa">
<emphasis box="[513,654,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">B. tenebrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is darker than the forewing). In the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[1284,1375,1328,1354]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clara">
<emphasis box="[1284,1375,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">B. clara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 17-22" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1811,1835]" captionTargetBox="[167,1416,230,1769]" captionTargetId="figure-31@8.[151,1435,201,1788]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 17-22. Bellulia spp., male genitalia. 17. B. kareni (after Fibiger 2008); 18. B. tenebrosa sp. n., holotype, Cambodia, genit. prep. hhl-3720-1; 19. B. clara sp. n., holotype, Cambodia, genit. prep. hhl-3728-1; 20. B. parabella (after Fibiger 2008); 21. B. hanae (after Fibiger 2008); 22. B. jiaxuanae sp. n., holotype, China, genit. prep. hhl-3537-1." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561455" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561455/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
) yuxta is larger than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[444,583,1364,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenebrosa">
<emphasis box="[444,583,1364,1390]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">B. tenebrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[637,738,1364,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kareni">
<emphasis box="[637,738,1364,1390]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">B. kareni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the ventral part of the tegumen is fused to the fultura superior with a prominent log-like process on each side, left shorter than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[891,993,1400,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kareni">
<emphasis box="[891,993,1400,1426]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">B. kareni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[1045,1184,1400,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenebrosa">
<emphasis box="[1045,1184,1400,1426]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">B. tenebrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and broader than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kareni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">B. kareni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.; in right valva, costal process (digitus) is thumb-shaped, prominently extending past the apex of valva (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[151,253,1472,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kareni">
<emphasis box="[151,253,1472,1498]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">B. kareni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the digitus horn-shaped, protrudes from the medial part of the costa, and extends only slightly bryong the apex of the valva, in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[387,527,1508,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenebrosa">
<emphasis box="[387,527,1508,1534]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">B. tenebrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is short and straight, cone-shaped, and does not beyong the apex of the valva). Aedeagus broader than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[445,585,1544,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenebrosa">
<emphasis box="[445,585,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">B. tenebrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[640,749,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[640,745,1544,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kareni">B. kareni</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
